    89→ *
    90→ * The `type` value may be a single MIME type string
    91→ * such as "application/json", an extension name
    92→ * such as "json", an argument list such as `"json", "html", "text/plain"`,
    93→ * or an array `["json", "html", "text/plain"]`. When a list
    94→ * or array is given, the _best_ match, if any is returned.
    95→ *
    96→ * Examples:
    97→ *
    98→ *     // Accept: text/html
    99→ *     req.accepts('html');
   100→ *     // => "html"
   101→ *
